  "SnippetModule": "data-preserve",
  "Extensibility": "<p class=\"opacity-80 mt-4 leading-relaxed\">The DOM isolator in <code>src/modules/attributes/preserve.ts</code> halts AST tree walking recursively. You can modify the compiler to ignore specific CSS namespaces identically.</p>",
  "Snippet": "<div class=\"tabs tabs-boxed mb-6\">\n    <a class=\"tab tab-lg\" data-class-tab-active=\"activeTab === 'A'\" data-on-click=\"activeTab = 'A'\">Morph Template A</a> \n    <a class=\"tab tab-lg\" data-class-tab-active=\"activeTab === 'B'\" data-on-click=\"activeTab = 'B'\">Morph Template B</a> \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"mt-4 p-8 bg-base-200 rounded-box border shadow-inner relative overflow-hidden\">\n    \n    <!-- Reactive Morph Target Container -->\n    <div id=\"morph-container\" class=\"transition-all duration-300\">\n        \n        <template data-if=\"activeTab === 'A'\">\n            <div class=\"bg-primary/20 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6 border-l-4 border-primary\">\n                <h3 class=\"font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-primary\">Context Template A Active</h3>\n                <p>The containing array structure completely shifts, yet the video player below remains completely unmutated by memory referencing.</p>\n            </div>\n        </template>\n\n        <template data-if=\"activeTab === 'B'\">\n            <div class=\"bg-secondary/20 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6 border-l-4 border-secondary\">\n                <h3 class=\"font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-secondary\">Context Template B Active</h3>\n                <p>Notice how the DOM structurally mutated, but the preserved element gracefully avoided virtual DOM diff destruction algorithms!</p>\n            </div>\n        </template>\n        \n        <!-- The Protected Node -->\n        <div data-preserve=\"demo-locked-video\" class=\"mockup-window border border-base-300 bg-neutral shadow-2xl\">\n            <div class=\"flex justify-center px-4 py-8 bg-neutral-content flex-col items-center\">\n                <h4 class=\"font-bold text-neutral text-xl\">Locked Element</h4>\n                <!-- Play around with native inputs inside preserved zones -->\n                <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Type here, switch tabs, state persists!\" class=\"input input-bordered w-full max-w-xs mt-4\">\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
